      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "How often are you working with binary data in 2-4 byte chunks? Really? A sane implementation would either work with it in BUFSIZ chunks (typically 4kb) or use other IO libraries that hides this detail. There&#39;s an entire library within the framework that&#39;s dedicated to help you work on buffers of data. You do a disservice to yourself and other maintainers of your code when you implement common operations without good reason (be it perf or other critical operation). These buffers are merely wrappers that operates on arrays, nothing more."
