      "body" : "@ptntialunrlsd Not actually. Before you performing <b>&amp;</b> operation on <code>byte</code> with 0xFF (<code>int</code>), JVM will cast the <code>byte</code> to <code>int</code> with <b>1 extended</b> or <b>0 extended</b> according the the leading bit first. There&#39;s no <b>unsigned byte</b> in Java, <code>byte</code>s are always signed."
